# CODEOWNERS — path-based review gate: the system, not the artifacts.
#
# Day-to-day product/design ARTIFACTS (prototypes, handoffs, briefs, sandbox work,
# About/Playbook/Resources content) are intentionally NOT listed here — they self-merge
# once CI is green, so designers and PMs can do their jobs without waiting on review.
# What IS listed is everything that defines or guards the SYSTEM itself: changing these
# in fundamental ways should never happen without an owner knowing.
#
# Enforced via the "protect-main" ruleset ("Require review from Code Owners" is ON).
# Both owners are listed on each line so either can approve the other's PR — GitHub
# never lets an author approve their own, so a PR touching an owned path always needs
# the *other* owner.

# ── Design-system core — shared CSS (components, tokens, chrome), doc pages, exports ──
